00:03:14.483 --> 00:03:17.988
But then, of course,
there'll be new features and

55
00:03:17.988 --> 00:03:22.141
functionalities that you'll
wanna add as an organization.

56
00:03:22.141 --> 00:03:25.734
So how do we go about adding
these new components?

57
00:03:25.734 --> 00:03:29.376
We can't let it be wild west,
that anybody can just go along and

58
00:03:29.376 --> 00:03:30.836
create a new component.

59
00:03:30.836 --> 00:03:33.543
Otherwise you'll have more and
more components being added and

60
00:03:33.543 --> 00:03:36.110
nobody will be looking after them and
it'll be a nightmare.

61
00:03:36.110 --> 00:03:40.223
So I'm in a little bit of a process for
adding your new components is worthwhile.

62
00:03:40.223 --> 00:03:45.413
Little bit upfront research before you
agree to a new component is great.

63
00:03:45.413 --> 00:03:48.766
Doesn't need to be much, you just
need to ask a series of questions.

64
00:03:48.766 --> 00:03:51.853
Can we use an existing component, right?

65
00:03:51.853 --> 00:03:55.772
It's amazing how often people wanna
jump in and create a new component

66
00:03:55.772 --> 00:04:00.102
when actually, all you need to do is
restyle an existing component, right?

67
00:04:03.293 --> 00:04:07.889
So oftentimes, you can actually
just reuse an existing one but

68
00:04:07.889 --> 00:04:10.845
add a layer of styling over the top of it.

69
00:04:10.845 --> 00:04:13.531
Other times it's,
can we revise an existing component?

70
00:04:13.531 --> 00:04:18.345
So could we change this component
to meet this new need and

71
00:04:18.345 --> 00:04:24.183
then roll it out to every other
occurrence of that component as well.

72
00:04:24.183 --> 00:04:27.771
And the other one that you need to ask is,
if you've got people spread across

73
00:04:27.771 --> 00:04:31.431
the organization is, is anyone working
on anything like this at the moment?

74
00:04:31.431 --> 00:04:35.294
[LAUGH] Cuz the number of times you've
got two designers working on the same

75
00:04:35.294 --> 00:04:38.907
component in different places and
nobody's talked to one another,

76
00:04:38.907 --> 00:04:40.044
I cannot express it.

77
00:04:40.044 --> 00:04:42.321
So just ask that question.

78
00:04:42.321 --> 00:04:46.326
Then it's a matter of
designing your new component,

79
00:04:46.326 --> 00:04:50.516
if there is a need for a one,
iterating it, testing it.

80
00:04:50.516 --> 00:04:53.379
Then it's handed across to development,
who code it up.

81
00:04:53.379 --> 00:04:58.673
You wanna document it, get it into
your ZeroHeight or Storybook system.

82
00:04:58.673 --> 00:05:03.951
And then just Make sure everybody
that is aware of this component,

83
00:05:03.951 --> 00:05:08.945
has a chance to review it and
to approve it, just to have a little

84
00:05:08.945 --> 00:05:14.146
bit of structure in place for
ensuring that it's not a wild west.

85
00:05:14.146 --> 00:05:17.855
Talking about version control,
we were talking about verse earlier and

86
00:05:17.855 --> 00:05:21.098
you were asking about naming
conventions and stuff like that.

87
00:05:21.098 --> 00:05:28.235
A little bit of vice around that, having a
clear versioning strategy, fairly obvious,

88
00:05:28.235 --> 00:05:33.959
establish a clear and consistent
approach for how you're gonna do it.

89
00:05:33.959 --> 00:05:37.946
Make sure you document any changes
that you're making as you go.

90
00:05:37.946 --> 00:05:42.274
I know it's boring writing documentation,
but it's so

91
00:05:42.274 --> 00:05:45.348
helpful when you get turnover of staff.

92
00:05:45.348 --> 00:05:51.055
And documentation should be more
than a comment in your code,

93
00:05:51.055 --> 00:05:53.921
developers, looking at you.

94
00:05:53.921 --> 00:05:57.138
[LAUGH] You should have
a rollout strategy, so

95
00:05:57.138 --> 00:06:00.448
what's your process of
rolling out new ones?

96
00:06:00.448 --> 00:06:05.115
And will they replace
the previous one universally?

97
00:06:05.115 --> 00:06:06.856
How are you gonna deal with that?

98
00:06:06.856 --> 00:06:10.768
A depreciation strategy
is worth having as well.

99
00:06:10.768 --> 00:06:13.676
So basically,
if you're gonna retire a component,

100
00:06:13.676 --> 00:06:15.626
what's it gonna be replaced with?

101
00:06:15.626 --> 00:06:18.251
What's your timeline for doing that?

102
00:06:18.251 --> 00:06:19.293
What's your alternative?

103
00:06:19.293 --> 00:06:22.941
How are you gonna communicate that
with the rest of the organization?

104
00:06:22.941 --> 00:06:27.819
And then, access to previous
versions is quite important.

105
00:06:27.819 --> 00:06:30.584
You might think you'll never
need it again, you will.

106
00:06:30.584 --> 00:06:35.182
So make sure it's available somewhere,
archived away.

107
00:06:35.182 --> 00:06:39.477
Adoption and communication is quite
key when it comes to design systems.

108
00:06:39.477 --> 00:06:44.106
So you gotta sell your design system,
cuz you create this design system,

109
00:06:44.106 --> 00:06:47.031
if nobody uses it,
you've wasted your time.

110
00:06:47.031 --> 00:06:51.902
So you wanna be communicating
the value of it, you wanna give people

111
00:06:51.902 --> 00:06:56.617
a sense of ownership and
the ability to influence its direction.

112
00:06:56.617 --> 00:07:00.865
There's nothing worse, designers, and
I think developers in my experience,

113
00:07:00.865 --> 00:07:02.365
but designers definitely,

114
00:07:02.365 --> 00:07:06.126
they will rebel majorly if you force
the design system on them, right?

115
00:07:06.126 --> 00:07:11.056
They throw a tantrum,
there's tears and it's horrible.

116
00:07:11.056 --> 00:07:13.152
So got to bring them along with you,
right?

117
00:07:13.152 --> 00:07:16.093
Get them involved in the creation process.

118
00:07:16.093 --> 00:07:18.301
It's great to have champions,

119
00:07:18.301 --> 00:07:23.960
some people that are gonna really champion
the design system and advocate for it.

120
00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:28.370
And you also wanna consider training and
support, especially if you use

121
00:07:28.370 --> 00:07:32.502
outside agencies and you need them
to work with your design system.

122
00:07:32.502 --> 00:07:35.832
So think about that and
how you're gonna do that.

